description: From the genus name translingual Coleus, from Latin coleus, from Ancient Greek κολεός (koleós, “sheath”) in reference to the manner in which the stamens are united.

definitionGroups.group: Any of certain plants in the mint family, many used as ornamentals for their colorful, variegated leaves, sometime included in genus Plectranthus (spurflowers), sometimes in  their own genus Coleus,

entries.meaning: especially, Plectranthus scutellarioides, also known as Coleus scutellarioides and Coleus blumei.
